ch.codebulb.lambdaomega.abstractions

Interface ReadonlyIndexedI<K,V>

  • All Superinterfaces:
    I<K,V>
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    IndexedI<K,V>, IndexedIFunctions<K,V>, IndexedIFunctionsS<K,V>, IndexedIS<K,V>, IndexedListI<K,V>, IndexedListIS<K,V>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    C, F, L, M, V2, V2.LV2

    public interface ReadonlyIndexedI<K,V>
extends I<K,V>
    An abstraction for a data structure with indexed (random) read-only access. This interface makes no assumptions about the data structure's ordering. It is loosely inspired by read-only methods of Map.
